benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/paymentMethods - Retrieve account payment methods

covered: Valid Request: Happy path (TC01) demonstrates successful retrieval with valid accountId.
Empty Response: TC08 validates empty array when account has no payment methods.
Query Parameters: Comprehensive coverage of various query parameters and edge cases (TC02-07, TC12, TC13).
Authorization: TC11 validates 401 for missing token.
Error Handling/Boundary: Accounts not found (TC09 404), invalid accountId (TC10/TC17 400), service unavailability (TC15/TC22), and timeouts (TC16).
Security: SQL injection (TC17) and XSS in pluginProperty (TC18).
Performance: Large dataset handling and response time check (TC14).
Regression & Recovery: Retry/partial failure scenarios (TC19) and backward compatibility/pluginInfo regression (TC20, TC21).
gaps: Pagination: No explicit tests for pagination behavior (page size, page tokens, links).
Rate Limiting: No tests validating throttling or rate limits.
Caching Behavior: No tests asserting caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) or cache invalidation.
Authorization nuance: No test for 403 Forbidden when user lacks sufficient permissions.
Edge coverage: Some error-path combinations (e.g., mixed valid/invalid parameters combined) could be expanded.
recommendations: Add explicit pagination tests: verify page size, page navigation, and correct total counts for large datasets.
Add rate limiting tests: simulate bursts and ensure proper handling (429 or throttling behavior).
Add caching tests: validate ETag/Cache-Control headers and conditional requests.
Add 403 Forbidden test to cover insufficient permissions scenarios.
Extend concurrency tests: simulate concurrent requests updating pluginInfo or audit fields to ensure idempotency.
